# Architecture Report: Modular AI Voice Agent (v2.0)

This report details the production-ready architecture of the Real Estate AI Voice Agent, designed for high-concurrency (20+ calls), low-latency performance, and modular extensibility.

## 🏗️ System Overview

The system follows a **Modular Orchestrated Pipeline** architecture. Instead of a monolithic script, the agent is broken into specialized, stateless modules coordinated by the **Pipecat** framework.

```mermaid
graph TD
    A[VoBiz/Telephony] <-->|WebSocket: PCM16| B[FastAPI Server]
    B <-->|Isolated Task| C[Pipecat Pipeline]
    subgraph Pipeline
        C1[STT Processor] --> C2[LLM Processor]
        C2 --> C3[TTS Processor]
    end
    C1 <-->|Local| D[Faster-Whisper]
    C2 <-->|API| E[Groq/Llama 3.1 8b]
    C3 <-->|Local| F[Kokoro-82M]
```

## 🧩 Core Components

### 1. Telephony Bridge ([telephony/vobiz.py](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/telephony/vobiz.py))
- **Transport**: FastAPI WebSocket endpoint (`/vobiz/stream`).
- **Data Format**: Bidirectional 16kHz Mono PCM16.
- **Scalability**: Uses `asyncio` TaskGroups to spawn an isolated Pipecat pipeline per connection.

### 2. Orchestration Layer ([flows/conversation.py](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/flows/conversation.py))
- **Framework**: `pipecat-ai`.
- **Processors**: Custom `FrameProcessor` implementations that wrap our internal modules into the pipeline lifecycle.
- **Greeting Logic**: Proactive greeting on `StartFrame` to ensure immediate engagement.

### 3. Speech-to-Text (`stt/`)
- **Engine**: `faster-whisper` (`small` model, `int8` quantization).
- **Optimization**: Buffers audio in 1-second chunks for transcription, optimizing for CPU-only environments.

### 4. Logic/Intelligence (`llm/`)
- **Engine**: Groq Cloud (`llama-3.1-8b-instant`).
- **Context**: Real-estate specialized system prompt ([prompt.txt](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/prompt.txt)) with domain restrictions.
- **Latency**: Sub-300ms time-to-first-token.

### 5. Text-to-Speech (`tts/`)
- **Engine**: `Kokoro-82M` (82M parameter local model).
- **Audio Prep**: Converts `float32` model output to `PCM16` (Int16) for hardware/VoIP compatibility.

## 🚀 Concurrency & Scaling (20+ Calls)

To meet the requirement for **20 concurrent calls**, the architecture implements:

1.  **Asynchronous Isolation**: Each call runs in its own `asyncio` task context within the FastAPI process.
2.  **I/O Offloading**: Heavy inference (STT/TTS) is offloaded to a background thread pool via `asyncio.to_thread` to prevent blocking the event loop.
3.  **Port Consolidation**: All 20 calls share a single WebSocket port (8000), simplifying networking and firewall rules.
4.  **CPU Efficiency**: Engines are quantized (`int8`) or lightweight (`Kokoro`), allowing multiple instances to share a high-vCPU VPS without exhaustion.

## 🔐 Security & Operations
- **Environment**: Sensitive keys (Groq) are stored in [.env](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/.env) and never pushed.
- **Monitoring**: [mic_test.py](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/mic_test.py) and [chat_test.py](file:///c:/Users/vishn/OneDrive/Desktop/Ai-voice%20agent/voice-agent-2.0/chat_test.py) provide local development verification independent of telephony.
- **Handoff**: Extensive [handoff_report.md](file:///C:/Users/vishn/.gemini/antigravity/brain/9c519fa3-4579-414c-a3d3-0b06eb8a61cd/handoff_report.md) provides troubleshooting for ngrok and deployment.

